HEADWORD: Plantage
<hw>Plant"age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A word used once by
Shakespeare to designate plants in general, or anything that is
planted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As true as steel, as <qex>plantage</qex> to the moon.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak. (Troil. iii. sc. 2).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plantain</ent>⟦br⟧
